<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-07T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-07T08:00:00-05:00" n="114" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d114">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.001 Chiang Kai-shek/8–745: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-07T20:00:00+07:00">August 7,
                                1945—8 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received August 7—1 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1302. The Generalissimo informed me this morning (supplementing my telegram
                        No. 1272 of August 2, 11 a.m.,<note n="81" xml:id="d114fn81">Not
                            printed.</note>) that he expects to be in a position to reply to the
                        suggested revision of the China Theater and SEAC (Southeastern Asia Command)
                        within the next 2 or 3 days.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hurley</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>